  "body": "The only way to specify the path to where data (same for cache and config) are suppose to live is either using the default path (that uses the $HOME variable) or by setting the XDG_DATA_HOME.\r\nThis is a problem if you not want to use the default path and can't use the XDG_DATA_HOME override (e.g. because of some dependency that uses the same variable)\r\n\r\nSuggestion:\r\nAdd a second way of overriding the default path. A new variable (something like `HELM_DATA_HOME`) that overrides both the default path AND the XDG_DATA_HOME variable.\r\n\r\nThis would be useful in github workflow which overwrites the HOME variable and attaches a volume to that path when executing a container such that plugins installed in the home folder at build time will be lost. ",
